Two people were taken to hospital following a fire at a block of flats in the east end of Glasgow. Two taken to hospital after Glasgow flat blaze Two people were taken to hospital following a fire at a block of flats in the east end of Glasgow.
Scottish Fire and Rescue Service crews were sent to tackle the fire, which broke out in a four-storey building in Onslow Drive, Dennistoun, at about 10:25.
The fire, which is thought to have been accidental, began in a bedroom on the first floor.
A man and a woman were taken to Glasgow Royal Infirmary for check-ups.
 